sec.p:
There were no significant differences in caregivers’ perception of therapy services based on the four age groups originally identified (Figure 1
). After combining the groups in two, younger (<10 years, n = 37) and older (10–18 years, n = 45), significant difference was detected in the Providing General Information
Scale (p = .03). Parents of the younger children reported that therapists provided general information to a moderate extent [M = 3.77; 95% confidence interval (CI) = 3.16–4.38], whereas parents of the older children reported receiving information to a small extent (M = 2.95, 95% CI = 2.47–3.43).
